item.description:
Notes: Let t be any real number and let P(x,y) be the terminal point on the unit circle defined by t. Then we define six functions of t:
 sin(t) = y; &ldquo;sine of t.&rdquo;
 cost(t) = x; &ldquo;cosine of t.&rdquo;
 tan(t) = (y/x); &ldquo;tangent of t.&rdquo;
 cot(t) = (x/y); &ldquo;cotangent of t.&rdquo;
 sec(t) = (1/x); &ldquo;secant of t.&rdquo;
 csc(t) = (1/y); &ldquo;cosecant of t.
